<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="227" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1427: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Representative of the President</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-24T19:00:00-04:00">May
                                        24, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>46. Your telegrams No. 53, May 19, 11 a.m., and No. 55, May 22, 4
                                p.m. In view of reports that President Somoza intends to visit
                                Tegucigalpa in order to discuss with President Carías a possible
                                solution of the boundary problem, I do not consider it wise for the
                                Commission or Mr. Ocheltree to take any action at this time.
                                Ocheltree’s proposed visit to Tegucigalpa should therefore be
                                deferred.</p>
                            <p>I think that the Commission should bear in mind the possibility of
                                carrying out the visit following the conversation between the two
                                presidents if it then appears that the visit should be
                                desirable.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>